 = \"PMID:20331540\", AUTHORS = \"Seidler U, Song P, Xiao F, Riederer B, Bachmann O, Chen M\", TITLE = \"Recent advances in the molecular and functional characterization of acid/base and electrolyte transporters in the basolateral membranes of gastric and duodenal epithelial cells.\", JOURNAL = c(\"Acta Physiol (Oxf) 201:3-20 (2011)\", \"DOI:10.1111/j.1748-1716.2010.02107.x\"))', 'map04971', 65, 0, 65, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `kegg-pathway-bottleneck`.`pathway_data` (`id`, `code`, `name`, `description`, `class`, `pathway_map`, `module`, `disease`, `dblinks`, `ko_pathway`, `reference`, `eukaryotes_count`, `prokaryotes_count`, `animals_count`, `plants_count`, `fungi_count`, `protists_count`, `bacteria_count`, `archaea_count`) VALUES (377, '04972', 'Pancreatic secretion', 'The pancreas performs both exocrine and endocrine functions. The exocrine pancreas consists of two parts, the acinar and duct cells. The primary functions of pancreatic acinar cells are to synthesize and secrete digestive enzymes. Stimulation of the cell by secretagogues such as acetylcholine (ACh) and cholecystokinin (CCK) causes the generation of an intracellular Ca2+ signal. This signal, in turn, triggers the fusion of the zymogen granules with the apical plasma membrane, leading to the polarised secretion of the enzymes. The major task of pancreatic duct cells is the secretion of fluid and bicarbonate ions (HCO3-), which neutralize the acidity of gastric contents that enter the duodenum. An increase in intracellular cAMP by secretin is one of the major signals of pancreatic HCO3- secretion. Activation of the CFTR Cl- channel and the CFTR-dependent Cl-/HCO3- exchange activities is responsible for cAMP-induced HCO3- secretion.', 'Organismal Systems; Digestive system', 'Pancreatic secretion', 'Type 2 diabetes mellitus, Hereditary pancreatitis, Pancreatic lipase deficiency', 'GO: 0030157', 'ko04972', 'list(REFERENCE = \"PMID:17850212\", AUTHORS = \"Petersen OH, Tepikin AV\", TITLE = \"Polarized calcium signaling in exocrine gland cells.\", JOURNAL = c(\"Annu Rev Physiol 70:273-99 (2008)\", \"DOI:10.1146/annurev.physiol.70.113006.100618\")), list(REFERENCE = \"PMID:20625287\", AUTHORS = \"Williams JA\", TITLE = \"Regulation of acinar cell function in the pancreas.\", JOURNAL = c(\"Curr Opin Gastroenterol 26:478-83 (2010)\", \"DOI:10.1097/MOG.0b013e32833d11c6\")), list(REFERENCE = \"PMID:16891880\", AUTHORS = \"